subjectAreas.name: Party
subjectAreas.description: This defines who you have trading relationships with and how. For example: customer & supplier along with their phone number and email.

entityGroups.name: Account
entityGroups.description: Example Entities included: Account, Account Contact, Bill Frequency

classConcepts.name: Account
classConcepts.description: How the party want to interact with your enterprise e.g. have multiple billing accounts

classConcepts.name: Account Contact
classConcepts.description: An individual who has a role specific to an Account.

classConcepts.name: Account Contact Role
classConcepts.description: What role does a contact play on an account e.g. decision maker, influencer

classConcepts.name: Account Partner
classConcepts.description: State what partner (account) is related to/have access to another account

classConcepts.name: Billing Frequency
classConcepts.description: Describes a period of time used for recurring bills e.g. monthly or semi-monthly

entityGroups.name: Contact Point
entityGroups.description: Example Entities included: Contact Point, Contact Consent, Contact Channel

classConcepts.name: Contact Point Address
classConcepts.description: Mailing address for a party e.g. 123 Main St, Big City, CA12345, USA

classConcepts.name: Contact Point Email
classConcepts.description: Email address for a party e.g. email info@northerntrailoutfitters.com

classConcepts.name: Contact Point Phone
classConcepts.description: Phone number for a party e.g. phone 123-4567

classConcepts.name: Contact Point
classConcepts.description: All contact points for a party e.g. phone 123-4567, email info@northerntrailoutfitters.com

classConcepts.name: Party Web Address
classConcepts.description: What is the Web URL for the Party

classConcepts.name: Contact Point Type
classConcepts.description: Contain the fixed list of types a contact point can be of e.g. phone, email

classConcepts.name: Contact Point Social
classConcepts.description: Social handle for a party e.g. trustednews at twitter

classConcepts.name: Contact Point Location
classConcepts.description: Physical location for a party e.g. party Northern Trail Outfitters at Standford Shopping Mall

classConcepts.name: Contact Point App
classConcepts.description: Software Application for a party and optionally on a specific device e.g. John Doe have Strava App on device iPhone123

entityGroups.name: Party Role
entityGroups.description: Example Entities included: Party Role, Buyer Role, Actor Role, Customer Role

classConcepts.name: Party Role
classConcepts.description: Trading roles a party may play at the same time i.e. Customer, Supplier, Seller, Competitor, Worker

classConcepts.name: Customer
classConcepts.description: Information about a party playing role of customer e.g. life time value, life cycle status

classConcepts.name: Seller
classConcepts.description: Information about a party playing role of seller e.g. customer satisfaction score

classConcepts.name: Supplier
classConcepts.description: Information about a party playing role of supplier e.g. vendor ranking

classConcepts.name: Competitor
classConcepts.description: Information about a party playing role of competitor e.g. strength (in products), weaknesses (in offerings), opportunities (to overtake), threats (to our business)

classConcepts.name: Customer Status History
classConcepts.description: History of when customer changed frome one status to another

entityGroups.name: Lead
entityGroups.description: Example Entities included: Lead, Lead Status, Lead Source

classConcepts.name: Lead
classConcepts.description: A person or company that showed interest in the company's products

entityGroups.name: Party
entityGroups.description: Example Entities included: Organization, Individual, Affiliate Group, Uncategorized

classConcepts.name: Party
classConcepts.description: A unified, in system, definition of who you are dealing with e.g. John Doe, Northern Trail Outfitters and can be of different types e.g. individual, business, affiliation group.

classConcepts.name: Individual
classConcepts.description: Represent the person you are, or will be, dealing with using the system

classConcepts.name: Household
classConcepts.description: A combination of people, normally recorded in the system for marketing or service purposes

classConcepts.name: Internal Business Unit
classConcepts.description: Defining a part of your own internal organization. May be anything from a holding company, a line of business, a country division, a department and for which you may want to track e.g. if it is a legal entity, default GL Code, profit-and-loss etc against.

classConcepts.name: Uncategorized Party
classConcepts.description: A party we may be, or will be, dealing with but we do not know who they are yet e.g. Social Handle 'TrustedNews' which we do not yet know if a person or a business but complain about our company so we want to log a case to investigate further. E.g. an ord

classConcepts.name: Party Additional Name
classConcepts.description: Under what name is a person also known as( AKA), under what alternate name is a business doing business as (DBA)

classConcepts.name: Person Language
classConcepts.description: Languages a person can comprehend and level of comprehension

classConcepts.name: Party Related Party
classConcepts.description: Relates any two parties together e.g. Jane and John Doe part of The Doe Household

classConcepts.name: Party Relationship Type
classConcepts.description: Define name of a relationship and how to read the relationship both ways e.g. household for / household member of

classConcepts.name: Party Identification
classConcepts.description: Set of ways to identify a party e.g. driving license, birth certificate

classConcepts.name: Person Employment
classConcepts.description: Information about an employee

classConcepts.name: Person Life Event
classConcepts.description: Major events a person had in their lives e.g. graudation date, marriage date

classConcepts.name: Person Education
classConcepts.description: Education a person has e.g. Phd, High School

subjectAreas.name: Payment
subjectAreas.description: A submitted payment. Includes information about whether a submitted payment was successfully processed or not.

entityGroups.name: Payment
entityGroups.description: Example Entities included: Payment, Payment Group, Payment Authorization, Payment Gateway

classConcepts.name: Payment
classConcepts.description: An amount of currency paid.

classConcepts.name: Capture Payment
classConcepts.description: The transfer of money from the customer's account to the merchant's account.

classConcepts.name: Refund Payment
classConcepts.description: Represents a repayment made, typically to a customer who isnt satisfied with the goods or services purchased. Refunds are typically made after a payment has already been received from customers

classConcepts.name: Payment Policy
classConcepts.description: This entity stores policy information for an org or an account which can be used to automate the process of payment application to invoice based on business needs.

classConcepts.name: Refund Credit Memo Allocation
classConcepts.description: Facilitates applying/unapplying refund balance to a credit memo.

classConcepts.name: Refund Allocation
classConcepts.description: Facilitates applying/unapplying a capture payment, or a credit memo to a Refund Payment.

classConcepts.name: Payment Group
classConcepts.description: Payment Group provides a way to associate payments and payment gateway events, where the payment is not associated with a Sales Order.

classConcepts.name: Payment Treatment Method
classConcepts.description: Represents a specific algorithm or method to apply. For example - pay for taxes first, pay for charges first, pay for oldest due invoice first etc. It can also point to a rule based on which application can be done. Treatment has a method.

classConcepts.name: Payment Treatment
classConcepts.description: This entity has the information which controls the way in which payment can be applied based on a legal entity or workflow. A policy has multiple treatments associated.

classConcepts.name: Payment Authorization
classConcepts.description: An approval from the issuer of a payment instrument (usually a card), that the customer has sufficient funds to cover the cost of the transaction.

classConcepts.name: Payment Gateway Authorization Reversal Log
classConcepts.description: A log record of all requests made to financial institutions, made via the payment gateway, to cancel payment authorizations.

classConcepts.name: Payment Gateway Interaction Log
classConcepts.description: A log record of all messages exchanged with merchants made via the payment gateway, for authorizations and payments.

classConcepts.name: Payment Gateway Payment Log
classConcepts.description: A log record of all messages originating with financial institutions that previously provided payment authorizations, that payments have been deducted from customers' accounts.

classConcepts.name: Payment Gateway Authorization Log
classConcepts.description: A log record of all requests made to financial institutions, made via the payment gateway, to authorize payments.

classConcepts.name: Payment Gateway Interaction Type
classConcepts.description: Reasons for accessing the Payment Gateway, including authorization, Sale and Void.

classConcepts.name: Payment Gateway
classConcepts.description: Holds the payment gateway merchant details which are used to interact external payment systems.

classConcepts.name: Payment Gateway Provider
classConcepts.description: Stores class details needed for maintaining Apex adapter.

classConcepts.name: Payment Gateway Result Code
classConcepts.description: The response from the Payment Gateway.

classConcepts.name: Payment Application
classConcepts.description: The designation of part or all of a Payment to satisfy a claim on the payment funds.

classConcepts.name: Payment Invoice Application
classConcepts.description: Facilitates applying/unapplying payment balance to an Invoice.

classConcepts.name: Payment Allocation
classConcepts.description: A Payment Application may be further broken down, to allocate payment funds to one or more line items within an Invoice or Credit Memo

classConcepts.name: Payment Credit Memo Application
classConcepts.description: Facilitates applying/unapplying payment balance to a credit memo.

classConcepts.name: Payment Credit Memo Allocation
classConcepts.description: Facilitates applying a Payment Application to the line items of a Credit Memo.

classConcepts.name: Payment Invoice Allocation
classConcepts.description: Facilitates applying a Payment Application to the line items of an Invoice.

classConcepts.name: Refund Payment Allocation
classConcepts.description: Facilitates applying/unapplying refund balance to a payment.

classConcepts.name: Payment Authorization Reversal
classConcepts.description: An authorization reversal is a message that alerts the issuer that part or all of a sale has been cancelled and the authorization hold should be rescinded.

subjectAreas.name: Payment Method
subjectAreas.description: A method of paying for a product or service, like a credit card or check.

entityGroups.name: Payment Method
entityGroups.description: Example Entities included: Payment Method Type, Payment Card Tender, Digital Wallet Tender

classConcepts.name: Payment Method
classConcepts.description: A means by which a buyer compensates a seller for a purchased good or service.

classConcepts.name: Payment Method Type
classConcepts.description: The category of payment method, such as payment card, check or digital wallet.

classConcepts.name: Payment Card
classConcepts.description: A payment system issued by a financial institution to a customer that allows its owner (the cardholder) to access funds in designated bank accounts

classConcepts.name: Coupon
classConcepts.description: Payment in the form of a voucher entitling the holder to a discount for a particular product.

classConcepts.name: Credit Tender
classConcepts.description: Payment to the seller that results in an agreement to pay at a later date, usually via a credit account.

subjectAreas.name: Product
subjectAreas.description: Anything you plan to sell or any part of a product that needs to be tracked for service purposes. For example, you are selling a green tractor.

entityGroups.name: Product
entityGroups.description: Example Entities included: Product Type, Product Item, Product Attribute, Product Relation

classConcepts.name: Product
classConcepts.description: What is intended to be sold e.g. goods, services, bundles, made to order products.

classConcepts.name: Goods Product
classConcepts.description: Products you can touch e.g. cart of milk, pallet of coffee, mobile phone x model 1

classConcepts.name: Service Product
classConcepts.description: Products that are intangible e.g. labor, software subscription

classConcepts.name: Bundle Product
classConcepts.description: Product groups e.g. mobile phone package include phone, call plan and charger

classConcepts.name: Product Translation
classConcepts.description: Translated attributes for a product

classConcepts.name: Product Related Product
classConcepts.description: A grouping of products such as a product bundle

classConcepts.name: Product Relationship Type
classConcepts.description: What are the types of relationships available e.g. bundled with/bundled in, substitute for/substitute of

classConcepts.name: Product Image
classConcepts.description: Images of a product

classConcepts.name: Product Image Translation
classConcepts.description: Translated attributes for a product image

classConcepts.name: Brand
classConcepts.description: What is the brand of the product e.g. Snike shoes

entityGroups.name: Product Attribute
entityGroups.description: Example Entities included: Attribute Set, Attribute Set Attribute

classConcepts.name: Product Validity Time Period UOM
classConcepts.description: Standard units of measure for time, for example minute, second, hour and day

classConcepts.name: Product Collateral
classConcepts.description: Collateral for a product e.g. link to brochure one

classConcepts.name: Attribute Set Translation
classConcepts.description: Translated attributes for an attribute set

classConcepts.name: Attribute Translation
classConcepts.description: Translated attributes for an attribute

classConcepts.name: Attribute Value
classConcepts.description: A predefine set of values for a product attribute e.g. shoe lace length 10, 12, 14 centimeter

classConcepts.name: Attribute Value Translation
classConcepts.description: Translated attributes for an attribute value

classConcepts.name: Product Attribute Value
classConcepts.description: Assignment of an attribute value to a product e.g. shoe lace

classConcepts.name: Product Attribute Set
classConcepts.description: A set of attributes e.g. shoe attributes that are assigned to a particular instance of Product

classConcepts.name: Price Book Entry
classConcepts.description: A list of products and their prices.

classConcepts.name: Device User Session
classConcepts.description: A time-bound period when a person used a website or other service, also known as a Visit

entityGroups.name: Product Catalog
entityGroups.description: Example Entities included: Product Catalog, Product Catalog Category, Product Catalog Assignment

classConcepts.name: Product Category
classConcepts.description: A product may consist of many categories e.g. shoes, tshirts

classConcepts.name: Product Catalog
classConcepts.description: A catalog used for a certain business process e.g. inventory, merchandizing

classConcepts.name: Product Catalog Translation
classConcepts.description: Translated attributes for a product catalog

classConcepts.name: Product Category Translation
classConcepts.description: Translated attributes for a product category

classConcepts.name: Product Category Product
classConcepts.description: Assignment of product to categories e.g. the Nikedas shoe assigned to shoe and running categories

classConcepts.name: Product Category Attribute Set
classConcepts.description: Assignment of an Attribute Set to a Product Category e.g. the Shoe attribute set assigned to the Shoes category

subjectAreas.name: Sales Order
subjectAreas.description: A document generated by a seller to indicate the specific products/services a buyer will be receive during a sale.

entityGroups.name: Sales Order
entityGroups.description: Example Entities included: Sales Order, Opportunity, Payment Method

classConcepts.name: Order Delivery Method
classConcepts.description: Standardized methods for transferring purchased products or services to the destination of fulfillment. Delivery methods are characterized by the means of transportation used, and by the delivering organization or group.

classConcepts.name: Sales Order Payment Summary
classConcepts.description: One or more Payments having the same Payment Method, that have been applied to a single Sales Order.

classConcepts.name: Product Relationship Type
classConcepts.description: What are the types of relationships available e.g. bundled with/bundled in, substitute for/substitute of

classConcepts.name: Sales Channel
classConcepts.description: Which channel is used to sell goods e.g. Web Store, Retail Store, Street Faire

classConcepts.name: Sales Order Product
classConcepts.description: A component of a Sales Order that identifies a product or service that will be sold to the customer

classConcepts.name: Sales Channel Type
classConcepts.description: Standard ways of selling products such as web, retail, direct marketing, etc

classConcepts.name: Sales Order
classConcepts.description: An internal document generated by the seller, indicating that the customer is now ready to purchase products and services

classConcepts.name: Sales Order Status
classConcepts.description: The status of a Sales Order

classConcepts.name: Sales Order Segment
classConcepts.description: A sub-period of an overall subscription which has pricing associated with it

classConcepts.name: Sales Order Confirmation Status
classConcepts.description: Stages of customer approval and finalization of a Sales Order.

classConcepts.name: Sales Order Type
classConcepts.description: Classifies a Sales Order as a New, Renewal or Change order

classConcepts.name: Renewal Term
classConcepts.description: For renewal orders, the length of the renewal term

classConcepts.name: Sales Order Product Status
classConcepts.description: The status of a line component of a Sales Order

classConcepts.name: Sales Order Product Reason Category
classConcepts.description: Groupings of Sales Order Product Reasons, such as product related or service related

classConcepts.name: Sales Order Product Reason
classConcepts.description: The customer motive for ordering a product or service, such as replacement, new purchase, upgrade

classConcepts.name: Sales Order Price Adjustment
classConcepts.description: A change to the price of a Sales Order that is made before order fulfillment. A Sales Order Price Adjustment may be comprised of Sales Order Product Price Adjustments that allocate the overall adjustment amount to one or more of the products and services

classConcepts.name: Price Adjustment Group
classConcepts.description: Supertype of: Sales Order Price Adjustment, Sales Order Product Price Adjustment, and FulfillmentOrderProductPriceAdjustment

classConcepts.name: Sales Order Price Adjustment Type
classConcepts.description: Reasons for adjusting the price of an order such as promotional discount, or customer satisfaction issue

classConcepts.name: Price Adjustment Method
classConcepts.description: Defines how the adjustment will be calculated. Valid values used in Commerce Cloud are: percentage, fixed_price, amount, free, price_book_price, bonus, total_fixed_price, bonus_choice, percentage_off_options

classConcepts.name: Sales Order Product Tax
classConcepts.description: A tax on the price of a Sales Order Product.

classConcepts.name: Sales Order Tax
classConcepts.description: A charge that is imposed by a government entity for public purposes. Types are aligned to phases of the process: SalesOrderTax, FulfillmentProductTax and ShipmentProductTax

classConcepts.name: Sales Order Delivery Group
classConcepts.description: One or more Sales Order Products that share a common Sales Order Delivery Method, and Shipping Address

classConcepts.name: Sales Order Delivery Status
classConcepts.description: The progress of a delivery such as awaiting pickup, in progress or complete

classConcepts.name: Sales Order Product Group
classConcepts.description: Products may be grouped together for various reasons, such as products that should be shipped together. Every product in a Sales Order Product Group is not required to be a Sales Order Product.

classConcepts.name: Sales Order Product Group Type
classConcepts.description: Reasons for grouping products together on sales orders, for example products that ship together.

classConcepts.name: Sales Order Product Note
classConcepts.description: A document accompanying a Sales Order that lists the description, quantity of the goods to be delivered or other information.

classConcepts.name: Sales Order Change Log
classConcepts.description: Change log for sales order

classConcepts.name: Sales Order ChangeT ype
classConcepts.description: The reason for a revision of an earlier sales order, e.g. quantity change, new distributed adjustment, new line adjustment, etc.

subjectAreas.name: Shipment
subjectAreas.description: Tracking the physical packages actually shipped for an order.

entityGroups.name: Shipment
entityGroups.description: Example Entities included: Shipment, Shipment Package, Shipment Document, Shipment Product

classConcepts.name: Shipment
classConcepts.description: A quantity of goods sent together to a place, or the act of sending them

classConcepts.name: Shipment Status
classConcepts.description: The stage of a shipment. Possible values could be pre-transit, in transit, delayed, delivered

classConcepts.name: Shipping Method
classConcepts.description: A parcel of one or more items bundled together, so that they arrive at the customer's address as a single unit.

classConcepts.name: Shipment Product
classConcepts.description: An item on a list of one or more that comprises a shipment.

classConcepts.name: Shipment Document
classConcepts.description: A receipt, bill of lading or other document that is delivered with the shipment to explain the purchase or shipment contents.

classConcepts.name: Shipment Package
classConcepts.description: A parcel of one or more items bundled together, so that they arrive at the customer's address as a single unit.

classConcepts.name: Shipment Product Price Adjustment Tax
classConcepts.description: A tax on the price of a Sales Order Product.

classConcepts.name: Shipment Product Price Adjustment
classConcepts.description: A change to the price of an ordered product or service that is made after Fulfillment.
